|archivedate=2007-10-18}}</ref> On November 16, 2007, ''[[The Politico]]'' and the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' reported that due to rumors that Holsinger would be [[recess appointment|recess appointed]], [[Party leaders of the United States Senate|Senate Majority Leader]] [[Harry Reid]] would convene the chamber several times during the two-week Thanksgiving break, effectively avoiding adjourning the Senate and preventing any recess appointment.<ref>{{cite web
|date=November 16, 2007
|author= Bresnahan, John
|url= http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2007/11/16/politics/politico/thecrypt/main3516002.shtml
